 "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "During last weekly meeting we discussed the desire to see auto entries in changelog to be improved. Two main questions aspects came to mind\r\n\r\n- Ability to provide custom summary for the release.  Something like what we did (sometimes) before:  e.g. https://github.com/datalad/datalad/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#0130-june-23-2020---- . So would be nice to somehow be able to modify some perspective entry within CHANGELOG which would get plugged in into next release on top.  If not possible with auto \"natively\", we might need to hackup some auto extension.\r\n- Ability to provide custom changelog entry for each PR in the PR.  ATM it is a PR title (if I get right), but that one is a bit restrictive since should be short. For some changes it is desired to provide a more elaborate description beyond title.  Is that possible?\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5782/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5782/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}